Bilkul Shubham! Aapke diye gaye errors dhyan me rakhte hue, main aapko **AWS Free Tier par EKS cluster banane ke liye** ek **complete step-by-step guide** de raha hoon ‚Äî **sirf working and correct commands**, jisse students ko koi error na aaye.

---

## ‚úÖ **AWS Free Tier Compatible EKS Cluster Setup (Ubuntu EC2) ‚Äì Final Working Commands**

### üß∞ 1. **Install AWS CLI (skip if already installed and working)**

```bash
curl "https://awscli.amazonaws.com/awscli-exe-linux-x86_64.zip" -o "awscliv2.zip"
unzip awscliv2.zip
sudo ./aws/install --update
aws --version
```

---

### üîê 2. **Configure AWS Credentials (Access Key, Secret)**

```bash
aws configure
```

Enter:

* AWS Access Key ID
* AWS Secret Access Key
* Default region (e.g., `ap-south-1`)
* Default output format: `json`

---

### ‚öíÔ∏è 3. **Install `eksctl` (tool to create EKS cluster)**

```bash
curl --silent --location "https://github.com/eksctl-io/eksctl/releases/latest/download/eksctl_$(uname -s)_amd64.tar.gz" | tar xz -C /tmp
sudo mv /tmp/eksctl /usr/local/bin
eksctl version
```

‚úÖ Should return version like: `0.180.0`

---

### üß† 4. **Install `kubectl` (to interact with the cluster)**

```bash
curl -LO https://dl.k8s.io/release/v1.29.3/bin/linux/amd64/kubectl
chmod +x kubectl
sudo mv kubectl /usr/local/bin/
kubectl version --client
```

‚úÖ Should return: `Client Version: v1.29.3`

---

### ‚òÅÔ∏è 5. **Create EKS Cluster (Free Tier compatible)**

```bash
eksctl create cluster \
--name demo-cluster \
--region ap-south-1 \
--nodegroup-name demo-nodes \
--node-type t3.micro \
--nodes 2 \
--nodes-min 1 \
--nodes-max 2 \
--managed
```

> üïí This takes \~15 minutes. Let it complete fully.

---

### üîç 6. **Verify the Cluster**

```bash
kubectl get nodes
```

‚úÖ You should see something like:

```
NAME                                           STATUS   ROLES    AGE     VERSION
ip-192-168-xx-xx.ap-south-1.compute.internal   Ready    <none>   2m      v1.29.x
```

---

### üßº 7. **(Optional) Delete Cluster (when not needed)**

```bash
eksctl delete cluster --name demo-cluster --region ap-south-1
```

---

## ‚ö†Ô∏è Common Mistakes to Avoid (Based on Your Errors)

| Mistake                                        | Solution                                                                              |
| ---------------------------------------------- | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| `kubectl: No such file or directory`           | Download kubectl properly with correct version and move to `/usr/local/bin`           |
| `syntax error near unexpected token '<?xml'`   | You downloaded an HTML page instead of the actual binary (wrong URL or missing `-LO`) |
| `eksctl: command not found`                    | Didn't install or didn't move to `/usr/local/bin`                                     |
| Wrong region `south-ap-1`                      | Correct region code is `ap-south-1`                                                   |
| `curl: Failed to extract a sensible file name` | Missing `-LO` flag when using `curl`                                                  |

